problem_info.title: 3309. Maximum Possible Number by Binary Concatenation
test_examples: Example 1: Input: nums = [1,2,3] Output: 30 Explanation: Concatenate the numbers in the order [3, 1, 2] to get the result "11110", which is the binary representation of 30.
Example 2: Input: nums = [2,8,16] Output: 1296 Explanation: Concatenate the numbers in the order [2, 8, 16] to get the result "10100010000", which is the binary representation of 1296.
